thread.title: Aust dollar holds below US73c
thread.title_full: Aust dollar holds below US73c | Business Spectator

author: AAP
title: Aust dollar holds below US73c
text:
Strength in the US dollar has stripped away some gains made by the Australian dollar following upbeat comments from the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) about the local economy.
At 7am (AEDT), the currency was trading at US72.61c, down from US72.69c on Tuesday.
BK Asset Management managing director Kathy Lien said there was still a bit of continued optimism following the RBA's minutes, released on Tuesday, which indicated there wasn't any immediate risk of additional easing by the central bank.
"(And) they seem more comfortable with the exchange rate than the market anticipated," she said.
Ms Lien said the local unit had been trading much higher, but during the North American session the US dollar clawed back some of the gains.
